  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Harnessing the potential of oil to contribute to Uganda&apos;s peaceful development - Phase 2</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">80,000 direct beneficiaries (10,000 per district)
Civil society organisations at local and national level; district local government; women, men, children in oil affected communities; government ministries, departments, agencies; cultural and religious institutions; oil companies</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improved accountability and transparency to citizens in oil extraction and management.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project builds on Alert&apos;s previous work in Uganda, aiming to promote peaceful, sustainable and inclusive oil exploration and production in Uganda through working with Goverment, civil society, communities and oil companies.</narrative>
  </description>
